When the hash contains a single quote character, Firefox (version 20.0 on Ubuntu) will encode it as **%27** in the string **window.location.href**.  This variable provides the value of **current** when the function **checkUrl()** is run.  However the value of **this.fragment**  to which it is compared is got from whatever is passed to **Backbone.router.navigate()**.  If we encode the hash that is passed to this function with **encodeURIComponent()** (or even **encodeURI()**), even Firefox will not encode the single quote to **%27**.  So the variables **this.fragment** and **current** will always be different. 

Solution: Backbone should decode the URI components before comparing them because

``` javascript
decodeURIComponent("%27") = "'";
encodeURIComponent("'") = "'"; 
```

