I've been using this pattern when working with nested models and collections:

``` javascript
var Child =  Backbone.Model.extend({});

var Parent = Backbone.Model.extend({
    initialize: function() {
        this.child = new Child();
    },

    parse: function(resp) {
        console.log('in parse', this.child);

        this.child.set(resp.child);
        delete resp.child;

        return resp;
    }
});
```

I've seen this pattern recommended several times, and it's quite close to the [example in the documentation](http://backbonejs.org/#FAQ-nested). I've also seen it mentioned several times in the issues, e.g. by @caseywebdev in https://github.com/documentcloud/backbone/issues/1929#issuecomment-11446973. This pattern has worked great for me so far.

However, let's now say that I need to do something like this:

