Or you have to define your own collection class that inherits from Backbone.Collection and defines the "model" attribute to be MyModel. The first option is ugly and the second option is often overkill because the standard collection class will suffice for all other needs. Therefore it would be very useful to be able to say:

var myCollection = new Backbone.Collection( jsonArrayOfModels, { model : MyModel } );

