I'd like to see Backbone have better support when REST isn't being used in an application. Some of the methods (like Collection.create) have dependencies on the Backbone.sync and a URL isn't defined on an object an error is thrown.

Currently I've been using something like the following to skip trying to run sync operations when no URL is found:

``` js
(function (){
    var originalBackboneSync = Backbone.sync;
    Backbone.sync = function (method, model, options){ 
        var url = (!(model && model.url)) ? null : _.isFunction(model.url) && (model.url !== Backbone.Model.prototype.url) ? model.url() : null;
