When you create new view like this:

``` javascript
Backbone.View.extend({
                    id: 'someId',
});
```

Backbone will create new div element with id "someId". If there's already DOM element with that id, Backbone would NOT attach this view to #someId and I think it's not an optimal behavior.

That is possible to override with el: 

``` javascript
Backbone.View.extend({
                    el: $('#someId')
});
```

but that's not an option if #someId is not available  at the moment of a view object creation. So I propose this little change to the make method: 

``` javascript

make : function(tagName, attributes, content) 
    {
         # addition
     if ('undefined' != typeof this.id)
     {
         var eElem = $('#' + this.id);
         if ( eElem.length > 0 ) return eElem;
     }
         # end of addition


     var el = document.createElement(tagName);
     if (attributes) $(el).attr(attributes);
     if (content) $(el).html(content);
     return el;
     }
```

